                        <date>First half of the 20th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓለ፡ አሜን፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#10vb">10vb</locus>, 16ra)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓለ፡ ዓለ፡ አሜን፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#14vb">14vb</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓ፡ አሜን፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን፡ </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#25rb">25rb</locus> )</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; a few lines on
                           the incipit page (alternating with black lines); two initial lines of the
                           beginning of the daily readings; initial line(s) of the sections of the
                           daily readings (homilies, absolution prayers, miracles and ʾarke);
                           selected words or parts of words in ʾarke; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 Names of the days indicating
                           daily readings are written in red pencil.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#62r">f. 62r</locus>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">: Donation note.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቶ፡ ወልደሥላሴ፡ ወብእሲቱ፡
                              ወለተዮሐንስ፡ ስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወስሙ[sic]፡ እሙ፡ ወለተሥላሴሙ[sic]፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለታቦተ፡
                              ቂርቆስ፡ አድግራት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት።</q>
                           <note> The note is written in the same poor hand as the
                           main text, in red. According to the note ʾato Walda Śǝllāse donated
                           the book to the Qirqos church in ʿĀddigrāt. Also the name of Walda
                              Śǝllāse's wife, Walatta Yoḥannǝs, father, Gabra Yoḥannǝs, and mother,
                              Walatta Śǝllāse, are mentioned. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#62r">f. 62r</locus>
                           <desc type="Exhortation">: Short exhortation to Christ for protection. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           
                           <note> The exhortation is written in a fine hand, in pen. A certain Gabra
                              Krǝstos entreats Christ to protect his life. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc>- Pen trials: <locus target="#62r">62r</locus></desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>-
                           Minor notes, writing exercises, doodles: on the leather cover of the
                           inner faces of both the boards, <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>, 17r,
                           19rv, 21va, 33rb, 61va, 62rv, 63rv.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days written in red pencil in a secondary hand, in the upper margins:
                              ዘሰኑይ: <locus target="#3r">fol. 3r</locus> ዘሠሉስ: <locus target="#13ra">fol. 13ra</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#21va">fol. 21va</locus>
                              ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#28va">fol. 28va</locus> ዘዓርብ: <locus target="#37va">fol. 37va</locus> ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#46vb">fol.
                                 46vb</locus> ዘእሑድ: <locus target="#54r">fol.
                           54r</locus>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
